
--------------------------------------Positions in CSS Assignment---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------






Task 1.-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Box Layout</title>
  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
    }
    .box {
      width: 50px;
      height: 50px;
      background-color: turquoise;
      position: absolute;
      text-align: center;
      line-height: 50px;
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 24px;
    }
    #a {
      left: 200px;
      top: 200px;
    }
    #b {
      left: 170px; /* 200 - 5 */
      top: 170px;   /* 200 - 5 */
    }
    #c {
      left: 230px; /* 200 + 5 + 50 */
      top: 170px;
    }
    #d {
      left: 170px;
      top: 230px; /* 200 + 5 + 50 */
    }
    #e {
      left: 230px;
      top: 230px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="a" class="box">A</div>
  <div id="b" class="box">B</div>
  <div id="c" class="box">C</div>
  <div id="d" class="box">D</div>
  <div id="e" class="box">E</div>
</body>
</html>



Task 2.-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


position: relative: Moves the element relative to its normal spot. It still takes up space in the layout.

position: absolute: Places the element exactly where specified, relative to the nearest positioned ancestor. Itâ€™s removed from the normal layout flow.








Task 3. -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Earth Card</title>
  <style>
    .card {
      width: 90%;
      max-width: 800px;
      border: 2px solid black;
      padding: 15px;
      background-color: #fdfbe9;
      margin: 20px auto;
      overflow: hidden; /* to clear float */
    }

    .card img {
      float: right;
      width: 200px;
      height: auto;
      margin-left: 15px;
      border: 1px solid #000;
    }

    .card h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="card">
    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1733506260469-8a6a07d95051?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDF8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D" alt="Colorful glass pattern">
    <h2>The Earth!!!</h2>
    <p>
      Nature is Earth's masterpiece, a symphony of life composed through millennia.
      Its landscapes whisper tales of ancient mountains, winding rivers, and flourishing forests,
      reminding us of the planet's boundless beauty. From delicate petals to towering redwoods,
      nature's artistry stirs awe and reconnects us to the essence of existence.
      Nature is Earth's masterpiece, a symphony of life composed through millennia.
      Its landscapes whisper tales of ancient mountains, winding rivers, and flourishing forests.
    </p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>



Task 4. -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Sticky Header</title>
  <style>
    body {
      
      margin: 0px 10px 0px 10px;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    header {
      background-color: #222;
      color: white;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 1000;
    }

    .logo {
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    nav a {
      color: gray;
      text-decoration: none;
      margin: 0 10px;
      font-size: 14px;
      justify-items: end;
    }

    nav_item {
      justify-items: end;
    }

    nav a.active,
    nav a:hover {
      color: white;
    }

    .cta {
      padding: 5px 10px;
      border-radius: 5px;
      color: gold;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: bold;
      border: 1px solid gold;
    }

    .content {
      padding: 20px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <div class="logo">LOGO</div>
    <nav class="nav_item">
